Sentencas: Gas phase transport is a very important electrode process in practical solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Gas Transport Impedance in Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: In this study, we have identified gas conversion impedance and gas diffusion impedance in the Mitsubishi segmented-in-series tubular solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Gas Transport Impedance in Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Gas conversion impedance is caused by the weak convection transport in the gas flow channel.
Titulo: Gas Transport Impedance in Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: It is observed that both the insufficient anode and cathode gas flow rates can result in the gas conversion impedance.
Titulo: Gas Transport Impedance in Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Gas conversion impedance appears at less than 0.1 Hz, and its magnitude strongly depends on the gas flow rates.
Titulo: Gas Transport Impedance in Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: It disappears when the gas flow rates of both the anode and cathode are improved sufficiently.
Titulo: Gas Transport Impedance in Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Anode gas diffusion through the porous substrate appears at similar to 0.5 Hz and dominates the overall diffusion impedance.
Titulo: Gas Transport Impedance in Segmented-in-Series Tubular Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Cathode gas diffusion through the porous current collecting layer appears at similar to 3 Hz, which significantly contributes to the overall gas diffusion impedance under low cathode oxygen partial pressures.
